column5: and you guys think 4 inches is safe?
Nobody puts on a show like Mother nature, truly impressive !!
I could only imagine the real sound of that. Spectacular!!!
At 1:52,it looked like a huge ice whale was coming up.  What an great video.
That's almost beyond comprehension.  Sort of like the whole of the Simcoe ice sheet flipping over at once.
That would be cool to see in person - at a very safe distance of course.
That is the power of mother nature for ya , can you just imagine being there to see and hear that !
That's a great video!  Felt like that on Simcoe yesterday when we where fishing near a big crack. The ice shifted so hard, I almost fell over...
I bet if there were trout under there, people would still try fishing it.  Pretty cool video though!  Going to have to find the full movie.
